Cash-based: All portfolios use <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Treasury Settlement Call Account" data-href="Treasury Settlement Call Account" href="pages/treasury-settlement-call-account.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">TS Account</a>'s for settlements.
Overnight funding default: Unless a term trade is booked, everything funds at ON rate.
Manual intervention: Term trades need manual mirror deals.
<br>Reactive controls: <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Reconciliation" data-href="Reconciliation" href="pages/reconciliation.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Reconciliations</a> run off <a data-href="GL" href="pages/gl.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">GL</a> (IM10 &amp; IM19) catch errors after EOD.
Limited transparency: True intraday liquidity position not visible to Treasury. <br>Heavy reliance on <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="SMART or Chameleon" data-href="SMART or Chameleon" href="pages/smart-or-chameleon.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Chameleon</a> and GL for operational control.
<br><a data-href="Exception Management" href=".html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Exception Management</a> is slow (post-EOD).
<br>No real-time funding attribution<a data-footref="2" href="#fn-2-e1a2aacfb8d239a9" class="footnote-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">[2]</a> (rates not decomposed into base/liquidity).
Complex structure of suspense accounts reduces visibility.
Treasury’s ability to manage intraday liquidity is constrained. <br><a rel="noopener nofollow" class="external-link is-unresolved" href="https://www.notion.so/2809ae4c7424808a9d81c402dbc1756f?v=2809ae4c742480cba177000cf0a3cefe" target="_self">https://www.notion.so/2809ae4c7424808a9d81c402dbc1756f?v=2809ae4c742480cba177000cf0a3cefe</a><a href="#fnref-1-e1a2aacfb8d239a9" class="footnote-backref footnote-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">↩︎</a><a href="#fnref-1-1-e1a2aacfb8d239a9" class="footnote-backref footnote-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">↩︎</a>
