<a data-href="GM" href="pages/gm.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">GM</a> (Global Markets): <br>Term trades manually booked in <a data-href="Murex" href="pages/murex.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Murex</a> using mirror deal functionality.
<br>Ensures <a data-href="GTSY" href="pages/gtsy.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">GTSY</a> portfolio has matched but opposite position.
<br><a data-href="FTP" href=".html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">FTP</a> rate applied. <br><a data-href="IBD" href="pages/ibd.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">IBD</a> / TTS (ZAR): <br>Term trades booked directly in <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="SMART or Chameleon" data-href="SMART or Chameleon" href="pages/smart-or-chameleon.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Chameleon</a>, mirrored to GTSY. <br><a data-href="IBD" href="pages/ibd.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">IBD</a> / TTS (Foreign Currency): Moving towards using Murex mirror deals. <br>Current gap:
FTP rates captured, but components (base vs <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Liquidity Premiums" data-href="Liquidity Premiums" href="pages/liquidity-premiums.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Liquidity Premium</a>) not split.
]]></description><link>pages/matched-maturity-funding.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">Pages/Matched Maturity Funding.md</guid><pubDate>Tue, 14 Oct 2025 11:04:29 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Liquidity Premiums]]></title><link>pages/liquidity-premiums.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">Pages/Liquidity Premiums.md</guid><pubDate>Tue, 14 Oct 2025 11:04:19 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[GM]]></title><link>pages/gm.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">Pages/GM.md</guid><pubDate>Tue, 14 Oct 2025 11:02:52 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[IBD]]></title><link>pages/ibd.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">Pages/IBD.md</guid><pubDate>Tue, 14 Oct 2025 11:02:46 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Treasury]]></title><description><![CDATA[
Desks don’t wire cash daily to Treasury.
Instead, Treasury applies <a data-href="FTP" href=".html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">FTP</a> charges/credits through <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="SMART or Chameleon" data-href="SMART or Chameleon" href="pages/smart-or-chameleon.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Chameleon</a>: If a desk has a negative balance → funding expense (charged interest). If a desk has a positive balance → funding income (credited interest). <br>Daily: Interest accrues in Chameleon on TS balances.<a data-footref="1" href="#fn-2-e1a2aacfb8d239a9" class="footnote-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">[2]</a>
<br>Month-end: Interest is capitalised (posted to P&amp;L).<a data-footref="2" href="#fn-3-e1a2aacfb8d239a9" class="footnote-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">[3]</a>
Lifecycle: Trade Day (): <br>Cashflow hits <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Treasury Settlement Call Account" data-href="Treasury Settlement Call Account" href="pages/treasury-settlement-call-account.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">TS Account</a>. EOD: <br>Balance charged <a data-href="FTP" href=".html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">FTP</a>. onward: accrues daily. Month-end: final interest posting. Desks don’t transfer actual cash to Treasury.
The funding cost is deducted from their P&amp;L.
When desks price trades, they must include funding costs (FTP) in the client rate. Example: Client loan at 7%.
FTP = 6%.
Desk margin = 1% (after paying Treasury). <br><a data-href="Different Desks" href="pages/different-desks.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Different Desks</a><a href="#fnref-1-e1a2aacfb8d239a9" class="footnote-backref footnote-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">↩︎</a>
